<headline>Severe Weather Statement issued May 24 at 10:28PM CDT until May 24 at 11:15PM CDT by NWS Amarillo</headline>
<description>...A SEVERE THUNDERSTORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 1115 PM CDT
FOR NORTHEASTERN OCHILTREE COUNTY...
At 1027 PM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 6 miles northwest
of Wolf Creek Park, or 9 miles southeast of Perryton, and is nearly
stationary.
HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and half dollar size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to roofs, siding, and trees is possible. Hail
damage to vehicles is expected.
Locations impacted include...
Perryton, Wolf Creek Park and Farnsworth.
HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX HAIL SIZE...1.25 IN
WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX WIND GUST...60 MPH</description>
<instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
